24/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Authorities have detained 244 illegal immigrants, mostly from Afghanistan, according to media reports Monday (23 June). 
A group of 185 Afghanis was caught shortly after entering the country from Iran, while police in Edirne arrested another 59 Afghanis, Chinese, Indians, Iranians, Pakistanis and Palestinians who were preparing to cross into Greece. 
Two Turkish nationals were detained for involvement in a human trafficking ring. 
Earlier this month, the US State Department criticised Turkey for failing to stem the tide of refugees. 
(AFP - 23/06/03)
